1
00:00:00,600 --> 00:00:02,400
And now, to the most urgent

2
00:00:02,400 --> 00:00:05,520
of the very many torments
afflicting modern life.

3
00:00:05,520 --> 00:00:07,480
What to do with all the
bloody photos on our phones:

4
00:00:07,480 --> 00:00:10,040
<i>JODY: Piece together</i>

5
00:00:10,040 --> 00:00:12,600
<i>your favourite memories,</i>
<i>literally.</i>

6
00:00:12,600 --> 00:00:15,640
<i>Create your own photo jigsaw</i>
<i>puzzle with PhotobookShop.</i>

7
00:00:15,640 --> 00:00:18,960
Yes, what better way to
cherish those special moments

8
00:00:18,960 --> 00:00:21,280
than turning them
into a jazzy jigsaw

9
00:00:21,280 --> 00:00:24,760
courtesy of the good folk
over at PhotobookShop,

10
00:00:24,760 --> 00:00:27,000
whose customers
are so enthused

11
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:28,200
with its many products

12
00:00:28,200 --> 00:00:30,640
they’ve taken to the
internet to say so:

13
00:00:30,640 --> 00:00:32,880
<i>SERON CHAU:</i>
<i>I feel like I’m holding a</i>

14
00:00:32,880 --> 00:00:34,400
<i>collectable artbook but</i>
<i>how funny and how surreal</i>

15
00:00:34,400 --> 00:00:36,920
<i>that all the art inside</i>
<i>this book is my own.</i>

16
00:00:36,920 --> 00:00:39,200
Yes, funny and surreal!

17
00:00:39,200 --> 00:00:40,440
And what about all those

18
00:00:40,440 --> 00:00:42,840
inspiring mottos you
might otherwise forget?

19
00:00:42,840 --> 00:00:45,000
<i>PRIYANKA PENDAM:</i>
<i>… I jumped on PhotobookShop</i>

20
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:48,520
<i>and ordered custom wall art</i>
<i>and look at the transformation</i>

21
00:00:48,520 --> 00:00:51,480
Advertising so good you
couldn’t pay for it.

22
00:00:51,480 --> 00:00:53,680
Except of course, it did,

23
00:00:53,680 --> 00:00:57,240
which one online influencer
Gracie McMahon discovered

24
00:00:57,240 --> 00:01:00,120
when PhotobookShop
tried to enlist her too

25
00:01:00,120 --> 00:01:02,600
with the offer of
free product in return

26
00:01:02,600 --> 00:01:05,880
for one Instagram
Reel and five photos,

27
00:01:05,880 --> 00:01:09,240
plus she might be interested
in a nice little commission

28
00:01:09,240 --> 00:01:10,920
on future sales.

29
00:01:10,920 --> 00:01:12,840
But hold on, what’s this?

30
00:01:12,840 --> 00:01:15,160
<i>Please ensure your</i>
<i>videos do not mention</i>

31
00:01:15,160 --> 00:01:16,320
<i>that the product is free,</i>

32
00:01:16,320 --> 00:01:18,480
<i>or sponsored,</i>
<i>or that PhotobookShop</i>

33
00:01:18,480 --> 00:01:22,520
<i>contacted you to create them</i>
<i>in exchange for products.</i>

34
00:01:22,520 --> 00:01:24,560
Offt, sneaky!

35
00:01:24,560 --> 00:01:25,800
And Gracie was having

36
00:01:25,800 --> 00:01:26,600
none of it,

37
00:01:26,600 --> 00:01:27,960
telling the Australian company

38
00:01:27,960 --> 00:01:30,040
behind PhotobookShop that:

39
00:01:30,040 --> 00:01:31,920
<i>… not disclosing</i>
<i>the partnership/</i>

40
00:01:31,920 --> 00:01:34,480
<i>gifting from a brand</i>
<i>is highly illegal.</i>

41
00:01:34,480 --> 00:01:37,040
<i>Please ensure you fix this …</i>

42
00:01:37,040 --> 00:01:39,560
And for good
measure she grassed.

43
00:01:39,560 --> 00:01:40,920
Prompting an investigation

44
00:01:40,920 --> 00:01:43,800
by the consumer watchdog,
which two weeks ago

45
00:01:43,800 --> 00:01:47,560
slapped the company with
a fine of almost $40,000.

46
00:01:47,560 --> 00:01:48,280
Never before

47
00:01:48,280 --> 00:01:50,480
has a business been held
to account for deceiving

48
00:01:50,480 --> 00:01:54,360
customers via covert online
advertising in this way.

49
00:01:54,360 --> 00:01:55,480
The Australian Competition

50
00:01:55,480 --> 00:01:57,280
and Consumer
Commission identifying

51
00:01:57,280 --> 00:01:59,280
more than 100 occasions

52
00:01:59,280 --> 00:02:02,080
on which PhotobookShop
ordered influencers

53
00:02:02,080 --> 00:02:05,160
to conceal payments
of up to $400

54
00:02:05,160 --> 00:02:08,640
in return for publishing
company-friendly propaganda.

55
00:02:08,640 --> 00:02:09,200
And yet,

56
00:02:09,200 --> 00:02:12,840
just last week we still
found posts like these.

57
00:02:12,840 --> 00:02:16,640
Lucy Hawkins promoting
her redecoration ideas

58
00:02:16,640 --> 00:02:19,680
and Rebecca Connolley
gushing over PhotobookShop’s

59
00:02:19,680 --> 00:02:21,520
seamless service.

60
00:02:21,520 --> 00:02:24,480
Lucy told us she had accepted
a gift from the company,

61
00:02:24,480 --> 00:02:27,480
while Rebecca would
not say either way.

62
00:02:27,480 --> 00:02:30,520
But after our impudent
emails and messages,

63
00:02:30,520 --> 00:02:32,960
both pulled down their posts.

64
00:02:32,960 --> 00:02:35,840
And when we spoke
to “oatcapbabe”

65
00:02:35,840 --> 00:02:38,120
whose name in the real
world is Priyanka Pendam

66
00:02:38,120 --> 00:02:39,680
she agreed:

67
00:02:39,680 --> 00:02:40,800
<i>… the disclosure may not have</i>

68
00:02:40,800 --> 00:02:42,480
<i>been as clear as it</i>
<i>should have been.</i>

69
00:02:42,480 --> 00:02:44,160
<i>Once this was brought</i>
<i>to my attention,</i>

70
00:02:44,160 --> 00:02:48,840
<i>I updated the post …</i>

71
00:02:48,840 --> 00:02:49,240
And to her credit,
indeed she did.

72
00:02:49,240 --> 00:02:51,760
In researching this story
we found dozens of posts

73
00:02:51,760 --> 00:02:54,600
on Instagram alone
plugging PhotobookShop

74
00:02:54,600 --> 00:02:58,200
and reaching a
potential 250,000 users,

75
00:02:58,200 --> 00:03:00,040
the genuine opinions
and the paid

76
00:03:00,040 --> 00:03:03,160
opinions, often utterly
indistinguishable.

77
00:03:03,160 --> 00:03:04,920
Which the company
must have missed

78
00:03:04,920 --> 00:03:07,800
in the clean-up program it
promised it had undertaken

79
00:03:07,800 --> 00:03:09,080
since the ACCC’s

80
00:03:09,080 --> 00:03:11,920
meddling:

81
00:03:11,920 --> 00:03:12,840
<i>… a small number of old</i>
<i>posts were identified …</i>

82
00:03:12,840 --> 00:03:15,360
<i>and have since been</i>
<i>corrected or taken down.</i>

83
00:03:15,360 --> 00:03:17,160
<i>Thank you for</i>
<i>pointing this out.</i>

84
00:03:17,160 --> 00:03:19,200
Glad to be of service, Peter.

85
00:03:19,200 --> 00:03:20,920
A spokesperson for the ACCC

86
00:03:20,920 --> 00:03:22,800
told us it expects
all businesses

87
00:03:22,800 --> 00:03:24,960
to comply with
Australian consumer law,

88
00:03:24,960 --> 00:03:28,200
which:

89
00:03:28,200 --> 00:03:30,000
<i>… applies as much</i>
<i>to the digital world</i>

90
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:31,440
<i>as it does to bricks</i>
<i>and mortar retailers …</i>

91
00:03:31,440 --> 00:03:34,320
Just two years ago the
ACCC found more than 80

92
00:03:34,320 --> 00:03:35,680
per cent of suspicious

93
00:03:35,680 --> 00:03:37,880
influencer posts
it investigated

94
00:03:37,880 --> 00:03:39,360
were potentially deceiving

95
00:03:39,360 --> 00:03:42,080
their followers in
this shabby way.

96
00:03:42,080 --> 00:03:44,640
Leaving the commission in
the unenviable position

97
00:03:44,640 --> 00:03:46,160
of playing whack-a-mole,

98
00:03:46,160 --> 00:03:46,960
trying to police

99
00:03:46,960 --> 00:03:50,560
a staggering number of
pretenders shilling for brands

100
00:03:50,560 --> 00:03:53,280
and hiding it from
their trusting audience

101
00:03:53,280 --> 00:03:56,040
almost makes you pine for
the dreaded mainstream media.
